cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a privacy-preserving photo encoding algorithm to address privacy concerns in photo sharing services. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper discusses server-side image transformations to conserve download bandwidth usage. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper mentions the accuracy of automated detection and recognition on the public part of the photo. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a technique to extract and encrypt a small component of the photo while preserving the remainder in a public part. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of photo sharing services and the privacy concerns associated with them.
